<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-325-941  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 325 941.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  March 14 1989 v8 n5 p48(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>PC-Globe Plus: maps and facts. (First Looks) (Comwell SystemsInc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Simon, Barry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Comwell Systems Inc. (products).andO;Product:   PC Globe Plus (Geographic information system).andO;Topic:     Software packagesMapsGeographyDemographyEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PC-Globe Plus: Maps and Facts PC-Globe put maps and related geographicalfacts at your fingertips.andP;  Now, PC-Globe Plus adds more data and support formore output devices.andP;  At $69, PC-Globe Plus is priced low enough for homeuse.andP;  And, for business use, detailed maps and large databases of geographic,economic, and demographic information make this lovely on-disk atlas asophisticated reference tool.andM;PC-Globe displays a world map, on which you can locate and highlightindividual countries and 18 country groupings (NATO, OPEC, and so forth).andP;  Auseful feature lets you colorcode the world map to show rankings in 82categories--from GNP per capita to the number of hospital beds per 1,000people.andM;Individual maps and information are available for 177 different countries.andO;You can make the country maps show cities, elevations, or notable features.andO;For each country, there are also four graphical displays and seven textpanels with information on a multitude of topics--from age distribution toeconomic data.andM;PC-Globe Plus has added support for EGA, VGA, and Hercules graphics to theoriginal product's CGA-only support.andP;  Also new is support for severalprinters, including the HP LaserJet (unfortunately only at 150 dots perinch), mouse support, and compatibility with the .PCX file format.andP;  Dropdownmenus have also been added.andM;Thanks to better data compression, PC-Globe Plus fits into less disk spacethan the original version.andP;  Still, if you want the power of an on-disk atlasat your fingertips, you'll have to be willing to part with 1.4MB of openhard-disk storage.andO;</TEXT></DOC>